Seventeen people sustained a series of injuries after four vehicles collided on the M4 North bound before the Moore Rd offramp yesterday (4 May) morning.Just before 7am Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find that four vehicles collided in the fast lanes. Two of the vehicles were taxis. Paramedics found that multiple people injured. More ambulances were dispatched to assist stabilising those hurt in the accident.Police are investigating the cause of the accident. &nbsp;